cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.SD 

This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques to analyze the transcripts of U.S. Congressional floor debates. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves the use of machine learning algorithms, which suggests that it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with social network analysis and discourse analysis, which could place it in cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing).
